gm method: when a request says 'edit project X' through skill Y's lens, the target is X not Y -- a user correction ('we're not editing the skill, we're editing the project') reframes scope without re-orienting from scratch. A large destructive reshaping (rip out a persistence layer + a learning subsystem) yields a high-tens PRD; cut hardest-first (rewrite the storage spine that every other row depends on) and smoke-test the core BEFORE rewriting the witness, so the witness rewrite measures real behavior. When git_finalize hits push-rebase-conflict (concurrent writer advanced remote), do NOT abort the session: fetch, rebase, resolve each conflict keeping your change + the remote's orthogonal improvement (e.g. a CI fix), re-run the witness post-rebase, then push via the git_push verb -- 'rebase and land alongside a concurrent writer' is the prescribed move, never blockedBy:external. Keep durable side-tables (snapshots/checkpoints) OUT of clearProjection so a rollback past a checkpoint event still finds the checkpoint.